import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_capitals = data.groupby('state').count().sort_values(by='city', ascending=False)
    state_capitals.plot(kind='bar', y='city', legend=None)
    plt.axhline(y=state_capitals['city'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max number of state capitals: {:.2f}'.format(state_capitals['city'].max()))
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    ax.axvline(x=data['lon'].mean(), color='r', label=f"Mean longitude: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(y=data['lat'].mean(), color='g', label=f"Mean latitude: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average longitude and latitude of all state capitals?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['lon'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['lon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lon'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of state capitals by longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
